do you spoil your dog if so how ex do you buy it clothes paint its nails or just give it lotsa love all of mine are spoiled rotten they have great house to live in a c on these hot days and it's nice and warm in the winter they take turns on the couch and on the bed with us they have great dog beds all over the house as well they get only the best dog food and vet care all are slim trim and extremely healthy they have a basketful of toys and balls and they drag them all over the house and yard constantly they get to play in the yard daily and go to the dog park several times a week they have their very own vehicle that all can ride in and plaster their wet noses all over the windows and no one cares they own humans who love them so much that they are selling their house to buy a new house with an even bigger yard for them to play in they get extra bites of food as treats and they are never fed junk i'd say yes they are but they all go to class and have good manners are expected to behave in the house while we are at work and in turn i will never ever dress them in clothes or paint their nails however i did paint a white skunk stripe down the back of my youngest he kept trying to help me paint the basement so i made him into a skunk dog grin yeah they're spoiled rotten but we get the better end of the deal with tail wags and kisses Hamster Pet skunk Skunk Dog Dog training Cat Comanche Care Bears Garfield Textile manufacturing Little Britain Domestic rabbit Japanese tea ceremony Doug The Shining (film) Clown The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Upholstery Fancy rat Gray Wolf Happy Tree Friends Shaggy dog story Rabies Ferret Aztec Plastic Nail (anatomy) The Empty Child Futurama (TV series - season 5) Casting Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Guinea pig Tire Bon Jovi Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Poker jargon Joke Sinfest Characters in the Smurfs The Great Race (Care Bears) Toy Story 2 Collyer brothers Kim Possible Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Butters Stotch Dod